The White House has announced that White House Counsel Greg Craig will be leaving his position and returning to private practice. President Obama praised Craig for his leadership and accomplishments, including confirming the first Latina justice on the Supreme Court and implementing strong ethics standards. Bob Bauer, currently a partner at Perkins Coie, will be taking over as White House Counsel. President Obama described Bauer as a trusted counselor and a respected advocate who is well-equipped to handle the responsibilities of the Counsel's office. The statement also includes a letter from Greg Craig to the President.